reviewText:
{3.5 stars}

While it's nothing really special, GONE is a tense, compelling crime thriller with its share of surprises and a lot of good chase scenes. Hard to predict--it probably won't end exactly as you think it will. It does have its share of unlikelihoods --e.g., the police won't even take a "Missing Person" report?--and general dumbnesses, but how many films in this genre do not have a few of those? Good script, however, the acting (sometimes over-acting) and directions are rather flat, obviously rehearsed, and TVland-perfect.

Worth 94 minutes if you like this sort of thing.
